1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,830
(Previously)
How's it going?

2
00:00:00,860 --> 00:00:01,940
I asked you to look into Lion.

3
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:03,040
Kanit sent you, didn't he?

4
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:06,010
You don't understand.

5
00:00:06,030 --> 00:00:07,170
You're an outsider.

6
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,200
One week.

7
00:00:08,570 --> 00:00:10,290
Go break it off with that flight attendant.

8
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,430
Stop talking to Lion.

9
00:00:12,450 --> 00:00:13,610
Why should I listen to you?

10
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,686
Your boyfriend is seeing a flight attendant
from another airline.

11
00:00:15,710 --> 00:00:18,030
From now on, I won't make
you work for me anymore.

12
00:00:18,210 --> 00:00:19,530
I'll consider it a donation to a stray dog.

13
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:20,810
I'M SORRY.

14
00:00:20,830 --> 00:00:23,010
Please consider forgiving Toto.

15
00:00:26,570 --> 00:00:27,850
You're playing hard to get, huh?

16
00:00:27,980 --> 00:00:29,070
You're gonna get it.

17
00:00:35,950 --> 00:00:37,220
Mom! Mom!

18
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:38,430
The clouds! The clouds!

19
00:00:40,020 --> 00:00:41,560
Uncle! Uncle!

20
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:42,580
The clouds!

21
00:00:42,890 --> 00:00:43,750
Go play with someone else.

22
00:00:43,770 --> 00:00:44,770
I want to sleep.

23
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,420
Auntie! Auntie!

24
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:47,980
The clouds!

25
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,640
Woo! Woo!

26
00:00:52,110 --> 00:00:53,690
Woo! Woo!

27
00:00:58,860 --> 00:00:59,860
Excuse me, Ma'am.

28
00:01:00,630 --> 00:01:01,990
Is there anything I can help with?

29
00:01:02,410 --> 00:01:03,200
Help with what?

30
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:05,050
It's normal for a kid to be playful.

31
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:07,880
But the other passengers are resting.

32
00:01:07,910 --> 00:01:09,680
He's disturbing them.

33
00:01:09,710 --> 00:01:10,840
For his safety,

34
00:01:10,860 --> 00:01:13,960
could you please have him sit down
and fasten his seatbelt?

35
00:01:14,170 --> 00:01:14,750
What?

36
00:01:14,940 --> 00:01:17,570
He's playful by nature.

37
00:01:17,610 --> 00:01:18,610
Can't you see?

38
00:01:18,730 --> 00:01:19,870
He's so cute.

39
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,600
How could you ask him to sit still?

40
00:01:22,490 --> 00:01:24,490
I'm afraid we have to. It's dangerous.

41
00:01:24,510 --> 00:01:26,760
Woo! Woo! Woo! Woo!

42
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,880
Want a lollipop?

43
00:01:30,330 --> 00:01:30,910
Want one?

44
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:33,170
But first, you have to
sit nicely for me, okay?

45
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:34,840
Come on, sit down.

46
00:01:37,990 --> 00:01:38,990
Good job.

47
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:41,590
Come on, fist bump.

48
00:01:42,190 --> 00:01:43,190
Pow!

49
00:01:44,130 --> 00:01:45,130
Great.

50
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,390
Thank you so much, sir.

51
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:56,300
"A Dog and A Plane"
(Episode 4)

52
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:07,960
Hey!

53
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:08,810
What do you think you're doing?

54
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:10,260
This area is for cabin crew.

55
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,396
Passengers aren't allowed in here.

56
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:13,000
You wouldn't talk to me.

57
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:15,380
I even bought a ticket
to get on this flight.

58
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:19,460
I have nothing to say to a scammer.

59
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,460
Hey!

60
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:23,970
I swear I didn't mean to lie to you.

61
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:25,820
Hey.

62
00:03:26,460 --> 00:03:27,980
Hurry up and say what you need to say.

63
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,720
I have to take care of the passengers.

64
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,450
I don't have any excuses.

65
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:33,130
I'm really sorry.

66
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:35,190
I want to apologize a hundred more times.

67
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:37,480
I misjudged Lion.

68
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:40,460
I didn't think
he'd go back on his word like that.

69
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:44,510
Besides, I know how much you love him.

70
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:46,220
So I wanted to give him another chance.

71
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:49,390
That was my decision to make.

72
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:50,560
You had no right.

73
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:53,360
Your job was only to spy on him
and report back to me,

74
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,840
not make decisions for me.

75
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:59,100
Knowing how much I love him was all the
more reason you should've told me the truth,

76
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:00,770
not lying and making
a fool of me like this.

77
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:02,520
Stop making excuses

78
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,560
and just admit it.

79
00:04:03,970 --> 00:04:05,150
All you care about is money.

80
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:06,550
Hey.

81
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,740
I swear I didn't take his money.

82
00:04:09,610 --> 00:04:11,070
I don't double-book myself.

83
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,910
You're my only boss.

84
00:04:15,330 --> 00:04:20,360
Do you realize that your good intentions
hurt me even more?

85
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:24,950
Okay.

86
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,680
I really didn't think it through.

87
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,240
Alright.

88
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,270
I'll stay on my knees
apologizing to you until we land.

89
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:31,690
Hey.

90
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:32,410
I'm sorry.

91
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:33,040
Get up!

92
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:33,610
It's my fault.

93
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:34,320
I'm sorry.

94
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:35,040
I'm sorry.

95
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:36,070
I'm sorry.

96
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,260
Look, I'm sorry.

97
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:38,060
Hey.

98
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:38,480
I'm really sorry.

99
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,660
Get up. This is embarrassing.

100
00:04:40,690 --> 00:04:41,320
I'm sorry.

101
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,360
Get up!

102
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,080
I'm not getting up

103
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,330
until you forgive me.

104
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:47,680
Let my guilt plunge to the ground with me.

105
00:04:47,710 --> 00:04:49,660
I'm not going down with you.

106
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,650
Get up already!

107
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:51,990
Fine! I forgive you! Come on!

108
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,040
Do you mean it?

109
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,360
Yeah.

110
00:04:56,610 --> 00:04:57,960
Don't ever do this again.

111
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,250
I don't like liars.

112
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:05,280
From now on, I promise that if anything
happens, I'll report it to you first, okay?

113
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,800
I won't take orders from anyone but you.

114
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,480
Mm.

115
00:05:10,730 --> 00:05:11,300
Go now.

116
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,320
We can talk later.

117
00:05:13,570 --> 00:05:14,570
Let's talk later.

118
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:21,970
Hey.

119
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:25,250
There's one more thing.

120
00:05:25,530 --> 00:05:26,530
What now?

121
00:05:29,210 --> 00:05:30,530
It's important.

122
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:34,210
Really important.

123
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:44,596
I feel kind of awkward telling you this,

124
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:46,590
but I think I should.

125
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:54,740
Can you buy me a ticket home?

126
00:05:55,370 --> 00:05:56,590
I've run out of money.

127
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,020
I just paid for my house,

128
00:05:58,050 --> 00:05:59,450
and I haven't gotten my salary yet.

129
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,490
Seriously?

130
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:01,660
Next time you want to be dramatic,

131
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,120
check your wallet first.

132
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:04,440
Please.

133
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:06,160
Fine, I'll take care of it.

134
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,760
Just go.

135
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,520
Go now.

136
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:11,770
Go.

137
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,270
I did some digging

138
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:23,970
and found out about
your boyfriend's side piece's family,

139
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:25,130
his parents' names,

140
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,540
the airline he works for,

141
00:06:26,570 --> 00:06:27,690
and what his house is like.

142
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,140
His name is Veha.

143
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:33,420
The guy you met
at your friend's bachelorette party.

144
00:06:33,790 --> 00:06:34,790
Remember him?

145
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:37,640
Ah.

146
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,120
No wonder

147
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,500
I got weird vibes from him when we met.

148
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,060
Yes.

149
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:44,200
He knew who I was.

150
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:52,090
I happen to be buying this bag too.

151
00:06:55,810 --> 00:06:57,970
Whatever I think is mine,

152
00:06:58,670 --> 00:07:00,400
I don't let anyone else take it easily.

153
00:07:00,430 --> 00:07:01,430
Who knows?

154
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,100
Your taste and mine are similar anyway.

155
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:08,630
That's the exact same energy as when
Muta met Nopnapha in Raeng Ngao.

156
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,360
What a slap in the face.

157
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:13,190
You know where he lives, right?

158
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:14,630
Why?

159
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:15,870
Are you going to ambush and slap him?

160
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:16,900
No.

161
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:18,810
I want to know what kind of person he is

162
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:19,750
and what's so great about him

163
00:07:19,790 --> 00:07:21,420
that makes Lion dare leave me for him.

164
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,970
I can definitely take you there,

165
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:26,170
but you have to follow my plan.

166
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:28,660
What do I have to do?

167
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,290
Since he's putting on an act for you,

168
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:32,820
you have to put on an act for him

169
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:34,190
and make it more convincing.

170
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:36,780
You have to pretend you're flying.

171
00:07:38,790 --> 00:07:39,950
Hey.

172
00:07:40,220 --> 00:07:41,560
It's your day off. You should be resting.

173
00:07:41,580 --> 00:07:43,820
You didn't have to drop me off.

174
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:44,420
Well,

175
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:47,210
I don't often get a chance
to spoil my boyfriend.

176
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:49,210
What time do you get off today?

177
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,120
Don't let him pick you up.

178
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:52,630
Pretend you'll get off late.

179
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,750
Make him think you're
definitely not around.

180
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:57,190
Act like you're really sad
to be away from him.

181
00:07:57,210 --> 00:07:59,400
Don't let him suspect you found out.

182
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:03,230
I've got four landings today.

183
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:04,420
I'll be back late for sure.

184
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,720
But it's okay. I can go home by myself.

185
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:09,720
You can go do your own thing, okay?

186
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:13,200
But I'd rather do it with you.

187
00:08:14,860 --> 00:08:16,970
I don't think I'll go anywhere.

188
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,356
I'll just stay home waiting for you.

189
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:19,380
I want to rest too.

190
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:20,920
Alright, once I get off,

191
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,440
I'll hurry to hug you.

192
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:25,440
I can't wait to see you then!

193
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,730
After that, you walk to the gate,

194
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:28,790
and quickly get out.

195
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:30,320
Once he falls for it,

196
00:08:30,340 --> 00:08:32,540
we'll catch him red-handed.

197
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:41,580
Alright, safe flights then.

198
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:42,980
Bye-bye.

199
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:56,520
Hey.

200
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,720
Huh?

201
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,361
Now that he thinks you'll be gone all day
and he can get away with it,

202
00:09:01,420 --> 00:09:04,200
he'll definitely go
running off to see Veha.

203
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:05,290
Trust me.

204
00:09:05,690 --> 00:09:06,250
Let's go.

205
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:07,270
Follow him.

206
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:26,470
SIDE PIECE'S CAR

207
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:28,480
What the hell?

208
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:36,840
Wow.

209
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,160
Nice paint job.

210
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,380
So red it looks like blood.

211
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:43,240
What the hell did you do?

212
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:44,700
What did you use to write on my car?

213
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,060
Calm down.

214
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:49,190
It's just pig's blood.

215
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,980
I just want you to know that
being a side piece is wrong.

216
00:09:53,130 --> 00:09:55,590
Kāmesu micchācārā.

217
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:56,880
You broke the third precept.

218
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:01,620
Engaging in adultery with
someone else's partner,

219
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:03,510
brings suffering and separation.

220
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,270
It clouds the mind and blinds wisdom.

221
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:06,810
Your life will not prosper.

222
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:09,766
And you will face the consequences
of karma in the third realm of hell,

223
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:10,790
such as

224
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:13,470
being tortured by climbing the thorny tree.

225
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:16,630
Sadhu.

226
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:20,700
I'm calling the cops on you!

227
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,610
Trespassing and property damage charges.

228
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:24,920
I'll sue you until you're broke.

229
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:29,970
No money. No escape. No payment.

230
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:34,570
Unless you want to settle this another way.

231
00:10:37,330 --> 00:10:38,970
If you don't have money, then go to jail.

232
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:41,010
Go ahead.

233
00:10:41,090 --> 00:10:42,610
But before I go to jail,

234
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,390
I'm going to expose you.

235
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:48,350
Veha Wongsuksawat is a homewrecker.

236
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:51,750
I'll scream it so everyone
in your condo hears. How about that?

237
00:10:53,370 --> 00:10:55,390
Veha is...

238
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,420
Stop!

239
00:10:59,710 --> 00:11:00,990
So you still have some shame.

240
00:11:01,450 --> 00:11:03,010
Why didn't you think before you did it?

241
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:04,900
Huh?

242
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:05,680
Side piece.

243
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:07,500
Side piece.

244
00:11:07,530 --> 00:11:10,640
Shoo wee doo wab.

245
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:12,640
Shoo [as in side piece].

246
00:11:12,690 --> 00:11:14,160
Side piece.

247
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:15,990
Side piece.

248
00:11:16,170 --> 00:11:18,890
Side piece.

249
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:50,380
When was the last time
we watched a movie together?

250
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:53,530
Oh, I think it's been a really long time.

251
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:54,780
Oh.

252
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:56,940
It's been that long
since I last took you to the movies?

253
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:57,970
Yeah.

254
00:11:58,410 --> 00:11:59,970
I'm sorry.

255
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:02,330
Wow.

256
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,200
What do you think?

257
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:10,970
Calm down!

258
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:12,100
Calm down.

259
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:14,620
Calm down.

260
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:15,200
Calm down, my ass!

261
00:12:15,230 --> 00:12:16,250
Let me help you.

262
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:17,560
Shh!

263
00:12:23,070 --> 00:12:24,790
Shh! Careful!

264
00:12:25,690 --> 00:12:26,790
Wow.

265
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,100
Damn.

266
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:31,120
He brought him to such a fancy cinema.

267
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:32,840
They're even watching it in bed.

268
00:12:33,490 --> 00:12:35,640
This is The Bed Cinema, right?

269
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:38,810
I guess they'll be watching,

270
00:12:39,340 --> 00:12:40,640
making out,

271
00:12:41,070 --> 00:12:42,220
and screaming at the same time.

272
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:42,990
Ahh!

273
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:44,020
Lion!

274
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:46,530
The ghost is here, Lion!

275
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,560
Lion!

276
00:12:47,770 --> 00:12:48,620
I'm scared!

277
00:12:48,650 --> 00:12:49,180
Lion!

278
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,220
Hey.

279
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:51,260
Stop building it up.

280
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:53,400
I'll go see it with my own eyes.

281
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:54,950
Hey.

282
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,790
Where am I supposed to get the money
for such a fancy experience?

